Google Suspends Street View Mapping in India After Police Raise Concerns

-- B y   K e t a k i   G o k h a l e
-- 
2011-06-21T10:12:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/google-india-stops-street-view-mapping-after-police-letter.html
Google Inc. (GOOG)  said it stopped
collecting data for its street view service in  India  after
receiving a letter from the police.  “We can confirm that we received a letter from the
commissioner of police regarding Street View,” Google said in
an e-mail today. “We are currently reviewing it and have
stopped our cars until we have a chance to answer any questions
or concerns the police have.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ketaki Gokhale in Mumbai at 
 kgokhale@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anand Krishnamoorthy at 
 anandk@bloomberg.net  